The April jobs report shows that the American economy is continuing to grow, with 263,000 new hires and a decrease in the unemployment rate to 3.6%, the lowest since 1969. President Trump's approval rating on the economy has reached a new high, with 56% of Americans saying he is doing a good job. Productivity in the first quarter of the year has also soared, driving the fastest yearly gain since 2010. The U.S. economy grew by 3.2% in the first quarter, surpassing expectations. Consumer spending increased significantly in March, but inflation remained low. Americans feel positive about their own finances, with optimism reaching levels not seen in over 16 years. Job offers and salaries are increasing, indicating a strong labor market. Retirees and workers are feeling more confident about their retirement finances. Hispanics are leading the surge in home ownership, income growth, and record low poverty rates. U.S. Steel plans to invest $1.2 billion in its steelmaking operations in Pennsylvania.